headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored a season-high 34 points, and Bennedict Mathurin added 21 points and 12 rebounds to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 119-110 victory over the Miami Heat on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Myles Turner scores 34, Pacers avenge Friday's loss to Miami with 119-110 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 25 points, Ty Jerome matched his career-high with 24 in place of Donovan Mitchell and the <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 25, Cavaliers become 4th team to start 15-0 with 128-114 win over Hornets

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 21 points, 10 assists and 10 rebounds to lead the Detroit Pistons over the Washington Wizards 124-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham's 4th triple-double of the season lifts the Pistons to a 124-104 rout of Washington

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson scored 20 points, and the Memphis Grizzlies built a 24-point lead in the fourth quarter in a 105-90 victory over the short-handed Denver Nuggets on Sunday in the opener of a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies beat short-handed Nuggets 105-90 in opener of a 2-game set in Memphis

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Shaedon Sharpe had 32 points, including a key 3-pointer down the stretch, and the Portland Trail Blazers withstood a late rally by the Atlanta Hawks for a 114-110 victory on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shaedon Sharpe scores 32 points and Trail Blazers withstand late Hawks rally for 114-10 win

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns returned from a one-game absence with 26 points, 15 rebounds and six assists, and the New York Knicks completed a two-game weekend sweep of the Brooklyn Nets with a 114-104 victory on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns returns with 26 points and 15 rebounds to lead the Knicks past the Nets 114-104

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored a season-high 28 points, Alperen Sengun had 20 points, 11 rebounds and 11 assists for his second triple-double this season and the Houston Rockets routed the Chicago Bulls 143-107 on Sunday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun records triple-double, VanVleet scores 28 in Rockets 143-107 rout of Bulls

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — P.J. Washington had 27 points and a career-high 17 rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks held off the Oklahoma City Thunder 121-119 on Sunday night without star guard Luka Doncic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington's 27 points, 17 rebounds help Mavericks edge Thunder 121-119 without injured Luka Doncic

headlines.description: — James Harden moved into second place on the NBA's career 3-point list and had 20 points and 11 assists to help the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Utah Jazz 116-105 on Sunday night to end a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden passes Allen for No. 2 spot on NBA's 3-point list, Clippers beat Jazz 116-105
